### File Structure
```
GymMembership/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── membership_plans.html
│   ├── plan_details.html
│   ├── class_schedule.html
│   ├── trainer_profiles.html
│   ├── trainer_detail.html
│   ├── pt_booking.html
│   ├── workout_records.html
│   └── log_workout.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   └── js/
│       └── scripts.js
│
└── data/
    ├── memberships.txt
    ├── classes.txt
    ├── trainers.txt
    ├── bookings.txt
    └── workouts.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing for all nine pages, reads and writes data to the local text files in the `data/` directory, processes user inputs, and renders HTML templates with the appropriate data. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here for simplicity and maintainability.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the nine pages specified in the requirements. These templates include the defined elements with their respective IDs and are rendered by `app.py`.

  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page template.
  - `membership_plans.html` — Membership Plans page template.
  - `plan_details.html` — Plan Details page template.
  - `class_schedule.html` — Class Schedule page template.
  - `trainer_profiles.html` — Trainer Profiles page template.
  - `trainer_detail.html` — Trainer Detail page template.
  - `pt_booking.html` — Personal Training Booking page template.
  - `workout_records.html` — Workout Records page template.
  - `log_workout.html` — Log Workout page template.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS and JavaScript files to style the web pages and add client-side interactivity.

  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across all pages.
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript file for client-side behaviors like button actions and dynamic filtering.

- **data/**  
  Directory holding all local text files used for data storage as per the specified formats. The backend reads from and writes to these files to manage memberships, classes, trainers, bookings, and workouts.

  - `memberships.txt` — Membership plans data.
  - `classes.txt` — Fitness classes data.
  - `trainers.txt` — Trainer profiles data.
  - `bookings.txt` — Personal training session bookings data.
  - `workouts.txt` — User workout records data.
